claim.claim-text:
1. A computer implemented method for generating an attribute from raw tradeline data from a plurality of credit data sources, the method comprising:
retrieving, with an attribute generation system, raw tradeline data from each of a plurality of credit data sources, wherein each of the plurality of credit data sources comprises a first subset of data and a second subset of data, and wherein the raw tradeline data is retrieved from the respective second subsets;
retrieving industry code data related to the second subsets of data from each of the plurality of credit data sources;
determining one or more tradeline characteristics associated with a subset of the retrieved industry code data to select as leveling characteristics for the second subsets of data, wherein the leveling characteristics are configured to yield substantially consistent tradeline data across the plurality of credit sources;
measuring a difference between the tradeline data from the second subsets across the plurality of credit sources using the selected leveling characteristics;
determining that the difference meets at least one predefined threshold; and
generating a leveled attribute for the second subsets of data using the selected leveling characteristics,
wherein the attribute generation system comprises a computer processor and an electronic memory storage.

2. The computer implemented method of claim 1, wherein determining one or more tradeline characteristics to select as leveling characteristics comprises:
designating a plurality of lowest common denominators from the industry code data related to the second subsets of data from each of the plurality of credit data sources as selected leveling characteristics, wherein the lowest common denominators comprise a minimum set of overlapping industry codes;
using the raw tradeline data from each of the plurality of credit data sources to generate test tradeline data using the selected leveling characteristics;
adjusting the selected leveling characteristics if the difference fails to meet the at least one pre-defined threshold; and
repeating said using and adjusting until the selected leveling characteristics generate a difference that meets the at least one pre-defined threshold.

4. The computer implemented method of claim 2 further comprising:
measuring a difference between a non-leveled attribute and the leveled attribute;
determining whether the difference meets at least one pre-defined threshold.

7. A computing system comprising:
a computing device including a processor;
a communications memory device in communication with the computing device, the communications memory device comprising instructions configured to receive raw tradeline data related to a plurality of credit data sources and to receive industry code data related to each of the plurality of credit data sources;
an attribute generation memory device in communication with the computing device, the attribute generation memory device comprising instructions configured to:
receive raw tradeline data from each of the plurality of credit data sources via the communications memory device comprising instructions, wherein each of the plurality of credit data sources comprises a first subset of data and a second subset of data, and wherein the raw tradeline data is retrieved from the respective second subsets;
receive industry code data related to the second subsets of data from each of the plurality of credit data sources via the communications memory device comprising instructions,
determine one or more tradeline characteristics associated with a subset of the retrieved industry code data to select as leveling characteristics for the second subsets of data, wherein the leveling characteristics are configured to yield substantially consistent tradeline data across the plurality of credit sources,
measure a difference between the tradeline data from the second subsets across the plurality of credit sources using the selected leveling characteristics,
determine that the difference meets at least one predefined threshold, and
generate a leveled attribute for the second subsets of data using the selected leveling characteristics.

8. The computing system of claim 7 wherein the attribute generation memory device comprises instructions further configured to determine one or more tradeline characteristics to select as leveling characteristics by:
designating a plurality of lowest common denominators from the industry code data related to the second subsets of data from each of the plurality of credit data sources as selected leveling characteristics, wherein the lowest common denominators comprise a minimum set of overlapping industry codes;
using the raw tradeline data from each of the plurality of credit data sources to generate leveled tradeline data using the selected leveling characteristics;
adjusting the selected leveling characteristics if the difference fails to meet the at least one pre-defined threshold; and
repeating said using and adjusting until the selected leveling characteristics generate a difference that meets the at least one pre-defined threshold.

11. The computing system of claim 8 wherein the attribute generation memory device comprises instructions further configured to determine one or more tradeline characteristics as leveling characteristics by:
measuring a difference between a non-leveled attribute and the leveled attribute;
determining whether the difference meets at least one pre-defined threshold.
